President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 20h00 tonight, Monday, 14 December 2020, on developments in relation to the country’s response to the coronavirus pandemic. * Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to address the country on Monday. Ramaphosa held a consultation with the National Coronavirus Command Council this weekend. READ: COVID-19: SA records 7,999 new cases It's expected that Ramaphosa will impose harsh restrictions. Last week, the country officially entered the second wave of the COVID-19 pandemic. South Africa's total cases now stand at almost 861,000.